    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Familiar Prejudices Against Immigrants</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kathleen Ambrose letter on September 28 article questions why parent would object to daughter being taught Spanish in elementary school due to 'invasion' of illegal immigrants on Long Island</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Re ''In Island's Wealthiest Area, Backlash Against the Poorest'' [Sept. 28]: I was surprised to read about a resident's objection to her daughter being taught Spanish on the elementary school level due to the ''invasion'' of illegal immigrants. Pedagogical theory attests to the fact that the younger children are when they begin to acquire a second language, the more likely they are to retain that knowledge. Current brain research in education also supports this theory. It makes one wonder if the students in Southampton who are also required to study violin on the elementary level are forced to do so as a result of an ''invasion'' of classical musicians in our area.</p>
        <p>Kathleen Ambrose  Southampton</p>
      </block>
